      "is_answer_order_important": false,
      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>Prostaglandin F<sub>2<i>α</i></sub>, a hormone that causes uterine contraction during childbirth, has the following structure. Are the two hydroxyl groups (–OH) on the cyclopentane ring cis or trans to each other? What about the two carbon chains attached to the ring?</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBZzhSIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--c0ce366a30e69f62d88a192ca7ca6038f2b434c4/OChem_04_02_007.jpg\" alt=\"The wedge-dash structure of Prostaglandin F 2 alpha.\">",
      "answers": [],
      "hints": [],
